'''Raimundo Nonato Tavares da Silva''', commonly known by the nickname '''Bob<U+00F4>''' (born November 28, 1962), is a retired [[Brazil]]ian professional [[association football|football]] [[midfielder|right midfielder]] and head coach, who played for several [[Campeonato Brasileiro S<U+00E9>rie A]] clubs.

==Playing career==
Born on November 28, 1962 in [[Senhor do Bonfim]],<ref name="cbf">{{cite web | title =Raimundo Nonato Tavares da Silva| url=http://200.159.15.35/registro/registro.aspx?s=86100 | accessdate =2008-09-16 | date =2007-11-16 | publisher=[[Brazilian Football Confederation]] |language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref name="gazetaesportivaprofile">{{cite web | title =Bob<U+00F4> - Raio-X| url=http://www.gazetaesportiva.net/idolos/futebol/bobo/raio_x.htm | accessdate =2008-09-16 | date =2002-09-23 | publisher=Gazeta Esportiva |language=Portuguese}}</ref> before becoming a professional player, Bob<U+00F4> played for local amateur club Bahia Jovem, then he joined [[Catuense Futebol|Catuense]]'s youth squad after the club's head coach, Jo<U+00E3>o Correia, observed him playing.<ref name="youthofficial">{{cite web | title =O Craque | url=http://www.bobo8.com.br/ocraque/index.php?idiomaid=1 | accessdate =2008-09-14 | publisher=Bob<U+00F4>'s official website |language=Portuguese }}</ref> In 1982, he started his professional career playing for Catuense, where he stayed through 1984.<ref name="enciclopedialance">{{cite book | first = | last =  | title = Enciclop<U+00E9>dia do Futebol Brasileiro Lance Volume 1 | publisher = Aret<U+00EA> Editorial S/A | location = Rio de Janeiro | year = 2001 | pages = 37| id = ISBN 8588651017}}</ref> In 1985, he joined [[Esporte Clube Bahia|Bahia]], where he won three times the [[Campeonato Baiano]] (in 1986, in 1987 and in 1988),<ref name="enciclopedialance"/> and also won the [[Campeonato Brasileiro S<U+00E9>rie A 1988|1988]] [[Campeonato Brasileiro S<U+00E9>rie A]],<ref name="enciclopedialance"/> scoring six goals in the competition, including two in the first leg of the final,<ref name="1988campeonatobrasileiro">{{cite web | title =Brazil 1988 Championship - II Copa Uni<U+00E3>o (1st level) | url=http://paginas.terra.com.br/esporte/rsssfbrasil/tables/br1988.htm | accessdate =2008-09-15 | date =2002-01-09 | publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]] }}</ref> and winning that year's [[Placar|Placar magazine]]'s [[Bola de Ouro|Bola de Prata]] award.<ref name="boladeprata19881989">{{cite web | title =Bola de Prata (Placar Magazine) | url=http://paginas.terra.com.br/esporte/rsssfbrasil/miscellaneous/bprata.htm | accessdate =2008-09-15 | date =2007-12-03 | publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]] }}</ref> He stayed at Bahia until 1989, when he was signed by [[S<U+00E3>o Paulo Futebol Clube|S<U+00E3>o Paulo]] for US$1 million.<ref name="miltonneves">{{cite web | title =Bob<U+00F4> (ex-meia do Bahia, S<U+00E3>o Paulo, Fla, Flu e Corinthians) | url=http://desenvolvimento.miltonneves.com.br/QFL/Conteudo.aspx?ID=61021 | accessdate =2008-09-14 | date =2008-09-02 | publisher=Milton Neves |language=Portuguese }}</ref> He scored three goals in the 18 Campeonato Brasileiro S<U+00E9>rie A games that he played for S<U+00E3>o Paulo,<ref name="saopaulo">{{cite web | title =S<U+00E3>o Paulo FC - All players in Brazilian Championship | url=http://paginas.terra.com.br/esporte/rsssfbrasil/miscellaneous/spjogbras.htm | accessdate =2008-09-18 | date =2007-12-05 | publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]] }}</ref> winning the 1989 Bola de Prata,<ref name="boladeprata19881989"/> and that year's [[Campeonato Paulista]].<ref name="enciclopedialance"/> After leaving S<U+00E3>o Paulo during the 1990 season, he played for [[Clube de Regatas do Flamengo|Flamengo]], winning [[Copa do Brasil 1990|that season]]'s [[Copa do Brasil]],<ref name="gazetaesportivaprofile"/> joining Flamengo's rivals, [[Fluminense Football Club|Fluminense]] in 1991, leaving the club in 1992, and playing for [[Sport Club Corinthians Paulista|Corinthians]] and [[Sport Club Internacional|Internacional]] in 1993.<ref name="enciclopedialance"/> In 1994, due to a judicial dispute with Corinthians, he ended the year without playing a game,<ref name="youthofficial"/> but in the following year, he resumed playing, after returning to Catuense.<ref name="enciclopedialance"/> In the same year, he returned to Bahia, retiring in 1997.<ref name="retirement">{{cite web | title =Bob<U+00F4> anuncia que vai deixar de jogar futebol| url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fol/esp/s2028014.htm | accessdate =2008-09-15 | date =2007-06-18 | publisher=[[Folha de S. Paulo|Folha Online]] |language=Portuguese}}</ref> Bob<U+00F4> played his farewell game on July 1, 1997 in a friendly tournament game between Bahia and [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]].<ref name="farewell">{{cite web | title =Torneio com Fla e Palmeiras marca despedida de Bob<U+00F4>| url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fol/esp/s2029127.htm | accessdate =2008-09-16 | date =1997-06-27 | publisher=[[Folha de S. Paulo|Folha Online]] |language=Portuguese}}</ref>

===National team===
Bob<U+00F4> played three games for the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]] in 1989, the first against [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]] on April 12, while the other two against [[Peru national football team|Peru]], on May 10 and on May 24, winning the first two games, the results were, respectively 2&ndash;0, 4&ndash;1 and 1&ndash;1.<ref name="brazil">{{cite web | title =Sele<U+00E7><U+00E3>o Brasileira (Brazilian National Team) 1988-1989 | url=http://paginas.terra.com.br/esporte/chancedegol/sel/brazil198889.htm | accessdate =2008-09-20 | date =2007-01-13 | publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]] }}</ref><ref name="enciclopediaselecao">{{cite book | first = | last =  | title = Sele<U+00E7><U+00E3>o Brasileira 1914-2006 | publisher = Mauad X | location = S<U+00E3>o Paulo | year = 2006 | pages = 236| id = ISBN 857478186X}}</ref>

==Non-playing career==
After retiring from playing football, Bob<U+00F4> worked as a sports commentator for [[Rede Bandeirantes]].<ref name="sportscommentator">{{cite web | title =Craques escalando craques| url=http://www.terra.com.br/istoe/politica/152521b.htm | accessdate =2008-09-21 | date =1998-12-23 | publisher=[[ISTO<U+00C9>|Isto<U+00C9>]] |language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref name="enciclopedialance"/> He worked as Bahia's youth squad head coach in 2000, then was promoted as the main team's head coach in 2002, winning the [[Campeonato do Nordeste]] in that year.<ref name="gazetaesportiva">{{cite web | title =Bob<U+00F4>| url=http://www.gazetaesportiva.net/idolos/futebol/bobo/abertura.htm | accessdate =2008-09-15 | date =2002-09-23 | publisher=Gazeta Esportiva |language=Portuguese}}</ref> He resigned as Bahia's head coach in April 2003,<ref name="showdebola">{{cite web | title =Brasileir<U+00E3>o 2008 - Balan<U+00E7>o da Rodada| url=http://www.showdebola.com.br/brasileirao/rodada06.php | accessdate =2008-09-22 | date =2003-04-28 | publisher=Show de Bola |language=Portuguese}}</ref> after his club was defeated by [[Paran<U+00E1> Clube|Paran<U+00E1>]] 3&ndash;1, a result that left the club in [[Campeonato Brasileiro S<U+00E9>rie A 2003|Campeonato Brasileiro S<U+00E9>rie A]]'s penultimate position.<ref name="seriea2003">{{cite web | title =Bob<U+00F4> sai e Evaristo pode assumir | url=http://noticias.uol.com.br/pelenet/bahia/ultimas/2003/04/28/ult1186u148.jhtm | accessdate =2008-09-15 | date =2003-04-28 | publisher=Pel<U+00E9>.net |language=Portuguese }}</ref> He was appointed as the club's director of football on March 4, 2005,<ref name="bahiadirectoroffootball">{{cite web | title =Bob<U+00F4> <U+00E9> o novo dirigente do Bahia | url=http://esportes.terra.com.br/futebol/estaduais2005/interna/0,,OI482241-EI4511,00.html | accessdate =2008-09-16 | date =2005-04-04 | publisher=[[Terra Networks|Terra]] |language=Portuguese }}</ref> resigning from the job in July of the same year.<ref name="bahiadirectoroffootballresigned">{{cite web | title =Bob<U+00F4> entrega cargo de diretor do Bahia | url=http://esportes.terra.com.br/interna/0,,OI601619-EI4848,00.html | accessdate =2008-09-16 | date =2005-07-22 | publisher=[[Terra Networks|Terra]] |language=Portuguese }}</ref> In 2006, Bob<U+00F4> worked as the host of Rede Bandeirantes' sports news show Esporte Total Bahia,<ref name="esportetotal">{{cite web | title =Novos dirigentes da Sudesb | url=http://www.sudesb.ba.gov.br/noticia.php?codigo=120&sc=imprensa | accessdate =2008-09-16 | date =2007-01-12 | publisher=SUDESB |language=Portuguese }}</ref> before being appointed in December by [[Bahia|Bahia state]]'s Governor [[Jaques Wagner]] as general director of SUDESB (Superintend<U+00EA>ncia dos Desportos do Estado da Bahia, meaning Bahia State's Sports Superintendency).<ref name="lancenet">{{cite web | title =Futuro governador da Bahia nomeia Bob<U+00F4> para assumir cargo | url=http://www.lancenet.com.br/noticias/06-12-14/19496.stm | accessdate =2008-09-14 | date =2006-12-14 | publisher=[[Lance!|Lancenet]] |language=Portuguese }}</ref><ref name="sudesb">{{cite web | title =Fonte Nova vai continuar interditada | url=http://www.sudesb.ba.gov.br/noticia.php?codigo=298&sc=index | accessdate =2008-09-14 | date =2007-11-26 | publisher=SUDESB |language=Portuguese }}</ref>

